answers.body_markdown:
FormControl has a `statusChanges` Observable you can [subscribe to][1].

So the code could look something like this:

			this.form.statusChanges
				.pipe(
					distinctUntilChanged()) // to reduce the noise
				.subscribe(() =&gt; {
					this.service.udpateFormIsValid(this.form.valid);
			});

  [1]: https://angular.io/api/forms/AbstractControl#statusChanges

